ratings.rComments: Most people will not get the class they expect when going in. The tests are pretty hard, and frustratingly so because the MC fixates on insignificant facts pulled from the reading. There is also something off putting about his personality, very full of himself and the people he knows. Tho, I will admit he is very accessible and likes what he does.
awesome class on military history
Lynn is the best teacher I've encountered in any university, bar none.  Passionate, endlessly helpful, and a deeply learned man.  Take the ride.

Easily the most interesting professor I have had at UIUC. Very passionate about the subject matter, lectures are interesting and I always looked forward to attending. As long as you attend lecture and do the readings from his book and the main textbook you will get an A. Described the Battle of Midway as "a cluster****."
Great professor!

I took both 401 and 251 with him and they were great courses.  I actually looked forward to going to his lectures.  That being said he can be a very polarizing man. If you have a good sense of humor and don't take things too seriously you will love his class.  That being said he is hard and if you dont read you are screwed.
TAKE THIS CLASS!

This class is horrible.  Just because a Professor swears does not make him interesting.  He openly admits that other colleagues in his field are wrong, with no evidence to support his claim. He is very arrogant and you have to buy a lot of books.  Notoriously HARD GRADER!

he goes off on tangents during class, almost never getting through the intended material, his power points are pointless and his handouts lack a lot of important information. his grading system is totally unfair, and his exams are practically impossible. he is pompous and arrogant. He chooses books that are too advanced for a 200 level course

Best lecturer I've ever had.  He's passionate about his work and it shows.  Even if I was sick I'd probably drag myself out of bed to go to class.  Reading is a must and the tests aren't bad if you study.  He is leaving after the spring and will be greatly missed so take his Hist 251 class!

Grading was very unreasonable.  He will let you know he doesn?t want to hear complaints at the start of class, so consider this when to begin class.  Needs to get over himself and books he writes, and constant hype about the Marine Corps.   Still good information in his class and I thought the books went well with the course.
Great professor always interesting really knows his stuff. Need to read tests are hard.  Uses current events as well as history u never want to skip his class!
His lecture is AWESOME. But the exam is quite challenging.
Kept things interesting and was very animated.  Final was quite tough
READ FOR THIS CLASS.. I didn't and its going to hurt me. This class was interesting but very hard. It was a bad choice for my elective
Great professor.  Really makes the class interesting with his passion for the subject and funny as well.  Best class I've taken.

Amazing lecturer, really loves the material and tries to make it interesting for the student. Brings out the social, political, and economic importance and context of military history. He can take a little bit of time to respond to questions, but he's generally supportive and tries to help. I highly recommend any course he's teaching.

Came into class excited but this is 1st time site has led me wrong.  Don't see what the big hype over this guy is.  Lectures are somewhat interesting, but very broad and unfocused compared to tests; he made it very clear he wanted nothing to do with the students or their grades; and dropping a couple f bombs isnt really that funny. Terrible TA also
This guy knows his stuff for sure! Lectures are helpful but I preferred just reading the book.  Some TAs are better than others. Study for exams and you'll do fine.

Lynn's TAs are very unfair with grading.  You write a whole paper and get no credit if it's good but it hurts you if it's bad. His tests are very very hard.  I went into this class excited and came out disappointed and very worried about my grade.
He told us not to complain about grades, eventhough some of his T.A.'s graded very hard and some graded easily.  It wasn't fair.  I did not enjoy this class, and I am a history major.

Professor Lynn is not a bad professor, but the nature of the course material makes class dry (at least for me, but I don't like history).  Also, he is not very sincere in his directions concerning tests.  For example, he might specify that ID test questions will come exclusively from lecture notes, but then will include several from other sources.
Prof. Lynn is a fantastic lecturer.  His lectures are absolutely captivating.  Sometimes he swears too much though.

Just have to keep up with the readings. Lecture outlines are put online. Two 4-6 page papers plus midterm and final. Tests consist of some tricky multiple choice and one essay of which he gives you two choices. Very into the class and he knows his freakin stuff. He has taught this class for years making it very organized.

An awesome guy who is definately not boring to listen to (He is not afraid to express his mind, especially by cursing). However, his tests are VERY HARD and based majorly on the readings (Which include 7 books, 1 in which hes written himself). Very smart man... but def not an easy A.

Extremely passionate about his subjects.  A literally world-famous scholar who wrote his own book for the course.  He occasionally will become quite tangental, but the stores that result are always fascinating

I didnt find it all *that* hard, we got the essays in advance.  The lectures are clear and he gives outline notes.  You cant not read or not go to class, but isnt the point of college to be challeneged.  A bit full of himself but a solid class all around and a magnificent lecturer.
A VERY hard class but interesting nonetheless.  Very pushy about buying his books though.  Hated when he was out of town and we had to listen and watch pre-recorded video lectures.

Senior thesis class for advanced comp requirement.  Not a blow-off.  Must read b/c he'll call on you, whether you volunteer or not.  Treats everyone in class like grad students, if you want an idea of  the maturity level of the class.  He is helpful as long as you put in the effort.  A good grade (A or B) is attainable as long as you work for it.
Although a difficult class, you will learn a LOT about military history. VERY energetic and fun, it is a worthwhile class but DEFINITLY not a blowoff. YOU WILL HAVE TO WORK, but it will be FUN.

Difficult, but engaging if you're up to the task. Fun, energetic lectures, can manage to make you intersted in something like horse formations. If you're looking for a blowoff class this isn't it, the tests are hard even when you've done the extensive readings and near impossible when you haven't.

Very hard, alot of assigned reading, but enjoyable lectures. The tests are hard, despite the fact that you get the essays beforehand. His lectures are awesome however, and I think everyone should take a Lynn class.

Great lecturer but difficult tests, 20 MP questions and an essay, with questions from anywhere in the book. The class requires +2000 pages of reading (including the research papers) but nobody does that much. Never boring, but expect to read a lot and memorize many names and dates if you want an A.

Professor Lynn is an engaging and interesting lecturer with a passion for his subject and a great sense of humor.  This is a class I never skipped and I still drop in to audit his class a year later, great Professor.

I wouldn't be as optimistic as everybody below, but he is interesting in a way thats similar to watching the history channel. 500 + pages of reading per test with questions (names dates) from anywhere.

The course is very hard and most would find the cirriculum uninteresting, but he makes the battles and wars of the past apply, in part, to today.  He also moves around a lot, swears, and tells a lot of jokes which make the lectures all the more fun.
New Grader System sucks, but not Professor Lynn's fault.  Always opinionated.  Very intellegent.  Teaches incredibly well.  A lot of reading, but worth it.
A great teacher, he is one of the great ones you remember long after you leave the University.
You'll learn more than any other teacher can tell you, worth taking for any history class.
Best teacher I ever had.  Passionate about his work.
No Comments
The best prof I had at U of I... just make sure to keep up with readings
best prof around
The best professor. Ever.
